translated: Jacobson, Tore Gustaf, hospital doctor, Vetlanda, born on January 3, 1904 in Gällistad, Älvsborg county, son of bank clerk B.W.J. and Eh n Strömbom. Married in 1930 to Elsa Maria Delphin. Children: Göran born in 1931, Lennart in 1934, Inger in 1937, Gunilla in 1945. He graduated from Skara High School in 1922, received his Bachelor of Medicine degree from Uppsala University in 1925, and his Medical Licentiate from the same university in 1930. He served as Assistant at the Pathology Institute in Uppsala from 1927-1928 and Assistant Doctor at the Obstetrics-Gynecology Clinic at the Academic Hospital in 1929-1930. He was awarded the rank of Naval Physician Grant from 1930-1932 and attained the rank of Second-Class Naval Physician in the reserve service in 1932 and first-class in 1940. He served as Acting Assistant and Temporary Assistant Doctor at the General Maternity Hospital as well as Acting Assistant and Temporary Assistant Physician at Södra BB in Stockholm in 1932. He worked as an Assistant Doctor at the Surgical Department of the Sahlgrén Hospital in 1933, Assistant at the General Maternity Hospital from 1933-1934, Temporary Second Assistant Physician at the Norrköping Hospital Surgical Department in 1934, Physician at the Karlshamn Hospital in 1935, Physician at the Eksjö Hospital from 1936-1939, First Assistant Physician there in 1939, Acting Senior Assistant Physician at the Surgical Department of S:t Göran's Hospital in 1940 and has served as a hospital doctor in Vetlanda since 1941.
